.TH "br_multicast_has_querier_anywhere" 9 "br_multicast_has_querier_anywhere" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
br_multicast_has_querier_anywhere \- Checks for a querier on a bridge
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" br_multicast_has_querier_anywhere
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int proto "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
The bridge port providing the bridge on which to check for a querier
.IP "proto" 12
The protocol family to check for: IGMP -> ETH_P_IP, MLD -> ETH_P_IPV6
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether the given interface has a bridge on top and if so returns
true if a valid querier exists anywhere on the bridged link layer.
Otherwise returns false.
